<subSubSection id="C310657D8F2DFFA6FF288D4C83DA69F0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB536F68F2DFFA6FF288D4C83DA69F0" blockId="7.[151,1436,525,730]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="B97EEAE48F2DFFA6FF288D4C867769BB" bold="true" box="[199,315,634,658]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
Though known only from a cave, this species is regarded as trogloxene, having no evident troglobiotic adaptations. Thorough searching of the cave did not result in a second finding of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0A4D758F2DFFA6FB998DAB83F2699C" box="[1142,1214,669,693]" class="Diplopoda" family="Julidae" genus="Megaphyllum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Julida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beroni">
<emphasis id="B97EEAE48F2DFFA6FB998DAB83F2699C" box="[1142,1214,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">beroni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus it could have been an accidental shelter in the cave of a very rare, endemic surface species (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9B4B078F2DFFA6FBEF8DF783C569F0" author="Beron" box="[1024,1161,705,729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Beron, P. (1994) Resultats des recherches biospeleologiques en Bulgarie de 1971 a 1994 et liste des animaux cavernicoles Bulgares. Serie Tranteeva - 1. Editions de la Federation bulgare de Speleologie, Sofia, 137 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Beron 
<number id="3DC224D18F2DFFA6FBA28DF783C569F0" box="[1101,1161,705,729]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
